---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const REACTOR_MODEL_GOOGLE_GROUP_URL = 'https://groups.google.com/g/reactor-model/';
---

<Layout>
  <main class="page-background">
    <div class="page">
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>Reactor Model of Computation</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          The reactor model is a way to structure concurrent, event-driven systems so that their
          behavior is deterministic, understandable, and predictable even in the presence of real-time
          interaction, distribution, and parallelism.
        </p>
        <div class="subscribe-cta" role="region" aria-label="Community mailing list">
          <div class="subscribe-cta-inner">
            <div class="subscribe-cta-copy">
              <span class="subscribe-cta-label">Reactor Model Community</span>
              <p class="subscribe-cta-text">
                Subscribe to our mailing list by joining the <a href={REACTOR_MODEL_GOOGLE_GROUP_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="subscribe-cta-link">reactor-model Google Group</a> for announcements and discussion.
              </p>
            </div>
            <a
              href={REACTOR_MODEL_GOOGLE_GROUP_URL}
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="subscribe-cta-button"
            >
              Subscribe on Google Groups
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <nav class="section-nav" aria-label="Page sections">
        <a href="#overview" class="section-nav-link">Overview</a>
        <a href="#projects" class="section-nav-link">Projects</a>
        <a href="#events" class="section-nav-link">Events</a>
      </nav>

      <section id="overview" class="overview">
        <h2>High-level overview</h2>
        <p>
          In the reactor model, systems are built from <strong>reactors</strong>: modular components
          that communicate via input and output ports. Reactors react to discrete events, which
          are tagged with logical time, and are scheduled according to clear rules that respect
          causality.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because reactions are triggered by time-stamped events rather than low-level threads or
          shared memory, the same design can be executed on a single machine, across a network, or on
          resource-constrained embedded platforms while preserving deterministic behavior (when
          desired). This makes the reactor model especially well-suited for
          <strong>cyber-physical systems</strong>, <strong>real-time control</strong>, and
          <strong>autonomous robotics</strong>.
        </p>
        <ul class="key-points">
          <li><strong>Modular structure</strong>: systems are composed from reactors with well-defined interfaces.</li>
          <li><strong>Logical time</strong>: events carry time tags, clarifying ordering and causality.</li>
          <li><strong>Deterministic concurrency</strong>: parallel execution is allowed without sacrificing predictable outcomes.</li>
          <li><strong>Platform versatility</strong>: the same model spans desktops, embedded devices, and distributed systems.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="projects" class="projects">
        <h2>Projects using the reactor model</h2>
        <div class="cards">
          <a
            class="card"
            href="https://lf-lang.org"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <h3>Lingua Franca (`lf-lang.org`)</h3>
            <p>
              Lingua Franca is a coordination language and toolchain for specifying reactor-based
              systems and generating efficient code for a variety of platforms and targets.
            </p>
          </a>

          <a
            class="card"
            href="https://www.xronos.com/#platform"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <h3>Xronos Platform</h3>
            <p>
              Xronos provides ready-to-deploy software infrastructure for scalable, safe,
              AI-driven robotics and mobility solutions, with a focus on deterministic development,
              real-time observability, and seamless integration.
            </p>
          </a>

          <a
            class="card"
            href="https://github.com/lf-lang/reactor-uc"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <h3>`reactor-uc` Runtime</h3>
            <p>
              `reactor-uc` is a lightweight reactor runtime targeted at distributed,
              resource-constrained embedded systems, supporting platforms such as Zephyr, RIOT,
              Raspberry Pi Pico, and POSIX hosts.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="events" class="events">
        <h2>Events</h2>
        <div class="cards">
          <a class="card" href="/events/">
            <h3>Events &amp; workshops</h3>
            <p>
              Past and upcoming workshops, including TCRS (Time-Centric Reactive Software)
              and ReCPS, and other events related to the reactor model.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <style>
		.page {
			max-width: 960px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
			font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
			line-height: 1.6;
			color: #111827;
		}

		.hero {
			margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		}

		.section-nav {
			display: flex;
			gap: 0.25rem;
			margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
			padding: 0.25rem;
			background: #f3f4f6;
			border-radius: 0.5rem;
			width: fit-content;
		}

		.section-nav-link {
			padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
			font-size: 0.9rem;
			font-weight: 500;
			color: #4b5563;
			text-decoration: none;
			border-radius: 0.375rem;
			transition: color 0.15s, background 0.15s;
		}

		.section-nav-link:hover {
			color: #111827;
			background: #fff;
			box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 3vw + 1.5rem, 3rem);
			margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
			letter-spacing: -0.03em;
		}

		.lead {
			font-size: 1.1rem;
			max-width: 46rem;
			color: #374151;
		}

		.subscribe-cta {
			margin-top: 1.75rem;
			max-width: 46rem;
			padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
			border-radius: 0.75rem;
			background: linear-gradient(135deg, #4338ca 0%, #6366f1 100%);
			box-shadow:
				0 4px 14px rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.35),
				0 2px 4px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
		}

		.subscribe-cta-inner {
			display: flex;
			flex-wrap: wrap;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: space-between;
			gap: 1.25rem;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-copy {
			flex: 1 1 16rem;
			min-width: 0;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-label {
			display: block;
			font-size: 0.7rem;
			font-weight: 700;
			letter-spacing: 0.08em;
			text-transform: uppercase;
			color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
			margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-text {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 1rem;
			line-height: 1.5;
			color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.96);
		}

		.subscribe-cta-link {
			color: #fff;
			font-weight: 600;
			text-decoration: underline;
			text-underline-offset: 3px;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-link:hover {
			color: #e0e7ff;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-button {
			display: inline-flex;
			align-items: center;
			justify-content: center;
			flex-shrink: 0;
			padding: 0.85rem 1.5rem;
			font-size: 1.05rem;
			font-weight: 600;
			color: #312e81 !important;
			background: #fff;
			border-radius: 0.5rem;
			text-decoration: none;
			box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.15);
			transition:
				background 0.15s,
				color 0.15s,
				transform 0.12s,
				box-shadow 0.12s;
			white-space: nowrap;
		}

		.subscribe-cta-button:hover {
			background: #eef2ff;
			color: #1e1b4b !important;
			transform: translateY(-1px);
			box-shadow: 0 4px 14px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.2);
		}

		.subscribe-cta-button:focus-visible {
			outline: 2px solid #eef2ff;
			outline-offset: 3px;
		}

		h2 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
			margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
			letter-spacing: -0.02em;
		}

		p {
			margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
			color: #374151;
		}

		.key-points {
			margin: 1rem 0 0;
			padding-left: 1.25rem;
			color: #374151;
		}

		.key-points li + li {
			margin-top: 0.25rem;
		}

		.overview,
		.projects,
		.events {
			scroll-margin-top: 4rem;
		}

		.projects,
		.events {
			margin-top: 3rem;
		}

		.cards {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
			gap: 1.25rem;
			margin-top: 1rem;
		}

		.card {
			display: block;
			padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
			border-radius: 0.75rem;
			border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
			background: #ffffff;
			text-decoration: none;
			color: inherit;
			box-shadow:
				0 1px 2px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.04),
				0 1px 3px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
			transition:
				transform 0.12s ease-out,
				box-shadow 0.12s ease-out,
				border-color 0.12s ease-out,
				background-color 0.12s ease-out;
		}

		.card h3 {
			margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
			font-size: 1.1rem;
			letter-spacing: -0.01em;
		}

		.card p {
			margin: 0;
			font-size: 0.95rem;
			color: #4b5563;
		}

		.card:hover {
			transform: translateY(-2px);
			border-color: #c4b5fd;
			box-shadow:
				0 8px 20px rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.12),
				0 4px 8px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
			background: #f9fafb;
		}

    @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
      .page {
        color: #e5e7eb;
      }
			.page-background {
				background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #1f2937 0, #020617 55%);
			}

			p,
			.key-points,
			.card p {
				color: #d1d5db;
			}

			.card {
				border-color: #1f2937;
				background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.9);
				box-shadow:
					0 1px 2px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.6),
					0 2px 6px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.9);
			}

			.card:hover {
				border-color: #a5b4fc;
				background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.95);
			}

			.section-nav {
				background: #1e293b;
			}

			.section-nav-link {
				color: #9ca3af;
			}

			.section-nav-link:hover {
				color: #e5e7eb;
				background: #334155;
				box-shadow: none;
			}

			.subscribe-cta {
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #312e81 0%, #4f46e5 100%);
				box-shadow:
					0 4px 18px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.35),
					0 2px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
			}

			.subscribe-cta-button {
				color: #1e1b4b !important;
				background: #f8fafc;
			}

			.subscribe-cta-button:hover {
				background: #e0e7ff;
				color: #0f172a !important;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
